The wizard is my main and first character, so I feel I have been on both sides of the fence. I leveled these toons from lvl 1 up to 65, with exception of chanter (wifes) and warrior (sons). <br>
<br>
Mages solo'ing constantly die/train zoneout/or use portals. Without a healer a charmed elemental is good for maybe 2 kills, unless you can get casters which would stretch pet abit longer if charm lasts. The time it takes for one of these elementals to heal even a bubble, while charmed is longer than charm lasts. Mages don't slow. When charm breaks mage get's summoned by the thing your fighting and it with  your former pet have you back at bind point before your have time to read the text saying charm broke. It can be done and you can get positive exp doing it, but it's much more effective grouping.<br>
<br>
I would like to address the all classes should be balanced issue. Gads, let's just make everyone one class so there can be not dispute about who is more powerful. Balance is a hard issue to quantify when your dealing with different skill sets, does wizard evac and teleports make them too powerful? <br>
<br>
